<div id="p37" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#2&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=37#p37">17-Nov-2007,Sat 05:44:53</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=3">higopi</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Expert Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"><img src="img/avatars/3.jpg" width="60" height="60" alt="" /></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Multi Langauge Typing select opiton</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi Vijay,<br /><br />Instead of handling it in JSP, you can achieve this in JavaScript itself.<br /><br />1) Include all the language and common js files of the converter in the &lt;HEAD&gt; section<br /><br /></p><div class="codebox"><div class="incqbox"><h4>Code:</h4><div class="scrollbox" style="height: 35em"><pre>&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/common.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript 
src=&quot;script/malayalam.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/telugu.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/kannada.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/oriya.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript 
src=&quot;script/gujarathi.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/punjabi.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/bengali.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/hindi.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/tamil.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src=&quot;script/english.js&quot;&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;</pre></div></div></div><p>2) Add the following script below the above code in the &lt;HEAD&gt; section. The below function switchLang will set the value of the language which comes in to immediate effect without re-submitting the page.<br /><br /></p><div class="codebox"><div class="incqbox"><h4>Code:</h4><div class="scrollbox" style="height: 18em"><pre>&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript&gt;
&lt;!--
function switchLang(val)
{
    lang = val;
    kbmode = &quot;roman&quot;;
    isChanged = false;
}
//--&gt;
&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;</pre></div></div></div><p>3) Add the list box for language selection where ever you want in your &lt;BODY&gt; section of your JSP page (of course you make this section to appear only for admin users in JSP).<br /><br /></p><div class="codebox"><div class="incqbox"><h4>Code:</h4><div class="scrollbox" style="height: 22.5em"><pre> &lt;select onchange='switchLang(this.value)' 
name=lansel&gt;
   &lt;option value=&quot;bengali&quot;&gt;Bengali
   &lt;option value=&quot;english&quot;&gt;English
   &lt;option value=&quot;gujarathi&quot;&gt;Gujarathi
   &lt;option value=&quot;hindi&quot;&gt;Hindi
   &lt;option value=&quot;kannada&quot;&gt;Kannada
   &lt;option value=&quot;malayalam&quot;&gt;Malayalam
   &lt;option value=&quot;oriya&quot;&gt;Oriya
   &lt;option value=&quot;punjabi&quot;&gt;Punjabi
   &lt;option value=&quot;tamil&quot; selected&gt;Tamil
   &lt;option value=&quot;telugu&quot;&gt;Telugu
&lt;/select&gt;</pre></div></div></div>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by higopi (13-Nov-2009,Fri 15:16:08)</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />Thanks,<br /><br />Gopi<br />Pick any two of &quot;Quality, Quick, Cheap&quot; service from me.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
